Charted at #46 on Billboard Hot 100 in October 1959. The Comets were nearing the end of their chart career by the time this song charted. Original Billboard review: "Infectious instrumental treatment of catchy theme, which had some success last year. Merits exposure." Another version by Bill Black's Combo bubbled under the Hot 100 at #114 in December 1962. Written by Joe Reisman. B-side is "Ooh! Look-a-There, Ain't She Pretty!".